                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Conversion Logic",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": For negative numbers, the function converts the last digit of the number into an overpunch character. This involves mapping the numeric digit to a specific character that represents both the digit and the negative sign."
